- Welcome / Account Created
- Email Verification
- Password Reset
- Invoice Generated
- Payment Received
- Service Provisioned
- Renewal Reminder (7-day, 3-day, 1-day)
- Suspension Warning
- Service Terminated

Provisioning Engine

üõ°Ô∏è Provisioning Engine (The "Brain")

Core Technology: CyberPanel (OpenLiteSpeed) running in Headless Mode via API.

1. Frontend (Next.js): The beautiful "Face". User interacts here.


2. Middleware (Golang): The "Manager". Validates requests and talks to CyberPanel.


3. Backend (CyberPanel): The "Worker". Executes heavy tasks silently.



User Action (Frontend)	Golang API (Backend)	CyberPanel Action (Server)

Create Website	POST /api/provision	createWebsite (Setup VirtualHost)
Check Status	GET /api/status	Monitor Service Status
Reset Password	POST /api/ftp/reset	changeFTPPassword
Suspend User	POST /api/suspend	suspendWebsite

> Note: The user NEVER sees the default CyberPanel UI. They only see your custom Premium Next.js Dashboard.



üåâ Database Management Strategy (The Bridge)

We use a Single Centralized PHPMyAdmin instance customized to handle both tiers:

Tier	Connection Type	How it works

Tier 0 (Free)	Local Socket	PHPMyAdmin connects to localhost (MariaDB Cluster)
Tier 1 (Premium)	Docker Network	PHPMyAdmin connects to Container IP (e.g., 172.18.0.5)

> Technical Detail: We will configure PHPMyAdmin's config.inc.php with AllowArbitraryServer = true to allow dynamic host connections.




